# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UBS FALSE-POSITIVE DOCUMENTATION
# Reviewed 2026-03-10 by GoldRiver after full manual inspection.
#
# WARNING: "Many console.* statements" (317)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — This is a CLI tool. console.log IS the user interface.
#   There is no browser; there is no logging framework to use.
#   Every console.* call is intentional CLI output. Do not suppress.
#
# WARNING: "Switch cases may be missing break" (6)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — All switch statements use `return` in every case branch.
#   Manual inspection of server.ts and monitor.ts confirmed zero fall-throughs.
#   UBS counts these because it looks for `break` but doesn't recognise `return`
#   as a terminator.
#
# WARNING: "Function declarations in blocks" (7)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — Manual inspection found zero function declarations inside
#   control-flow blocks. All function declarations are at module scope.
#   UBS appears to misparse certain TypeScript constructs as block-level
#   function declarations.
#
# WARNING: "Nested ternary operators" (4)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — The flagged lines are TypeScript type annotations with
#   optional chaining `?` in constructor parameter types
#   (e.g. `deps?: { ssh?: SSHManager; remote?: RemoteCommandRunner }`).
#   These are NOT ternary operators. UBS does not parse TypeScript types.
#
# WARNING: "Blocking dialogs" (3)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — The flagged usages are:
#   (1) cli/rollback.ts: a readline-based `async function prompt()` wrapper —
#       NOT window.prompt(). It is asynchronous and Node.js-safe.
#   (2) cli/index.ts:333: a console.log() call — not a dialog at all.
#   UBS pattern-matches on the identifier `prompt` regardless of context.
#
# WARNING: "Synchronous fs.*Sync calls" (4)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — These are intentional per the architectural design:
#   - readFileSync: reads small YAML config files (~1 KB) at startup
#   - writeFileSync / mkdirSync / chmodSync: one-time config file writes
#   - The pitch explicitly mandates synchronous SQLite (better-sqlite3)
#   Blocking I/O is acceptable for a local CLI tool processing tiny config files.
#
# INFO: "Explicit any types present" (2 — ssh.ts SSHStreamChannel.on)
#   FALSE POSITIVE — The two `any[]` annotations are on the `.on()` listener
#   signatures of an internal `SSHStreamChannel` interface that models the
#   Node.js EventEmitter pattern. TypeScript's own `EventEmitter.on()` type uses
#   `any[]` for the same reason: using `unknown[]` breaks contravariance for all
#   typed callbacks (e.g. `(chunk: Buffer) => void`). The `any` is scoped to a
#   private interface and annotated with `// eslint-disable-next-line`.
#
# INFO: "TypeScript compiler not detected"
#   FALSE POSITIVE — TypeScript IS installed (see devDependencies in package.json).
#   UBS is looking for a global `tsc`; we use `npx tsc` via the project's
#   local devDependency. Run `npm run typecheck` for TypeScript validation.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
